%F A000567 a(n) = n*(3*n-2).
%F A000567 a(n) = (3n-2)*(3n-1)*(3n)/((3n-1) + (3n-2) + (3n)), i.e., (the product of three consecutive numbers)/(their sum). a(1) = 1*2*3/(1+2+3), a(2) = 4*5*6/(4+5+6), etc. - _Amarnath Murthy_, Aug 29 2002
%F A000567 E.g.f.: exp(x)*(x+3*x^2). - _Paul Barry_, Jul 23 2003
%F A000567 G.f.: x*(1+5*x)/(1-x)^3. _Simon Plouffe_ in his 1992 dissertation
%F A000567 a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} (5*n - 4*k). - _Paul Barry_, Sep 06 2005
%F A000567 a(n) = n + 6*A000217(n-1). - _Floor van Lamoen_, Oct 14 2005
%F A000567 a(n) = C(n+1,2) + 5*C(n,2).
%F A000567 Starting (1, 8, 21, 40, 65, ...) = binomial transform of [1, 7, 6, 0, 0, 0, ...]. - _Gary W. Adamson_, Apr 30 2008
%F A000567 a(n) = 3*a(n-1) - 3*a(n-2) + a(n-3), a(0)=0, a(1)=1, a(2)=8. - _Jaume Oliver Lafont_, Dec 02 2008
%F A000567 a(n) = A000578(n) - A007531(n). - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Sep 18 2009
%F A000567 a(n) = a(n-1) + 6*n - 5 (with a(0)=0). - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Nov 20 2010
%F A000567 a(n) = 2*a(n-1) - a(n-2) + 6. - _Ant King_, Sep 01 2011
%F A000567 a(n) = A000217(n) + 5*A000217(n-1). - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Nov 20 2010
%F A000567 a(n) = (A185212(n) - 1) / 4. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Dec 20 2012
%F A000567 a(n) = A174709(6n). - _Philippe Deléham_, Mar 26 2013
%F A000567 a(n) = (2*n-1)^2 - (n-1)^2. - _Ivan N. Ianakiev_, Apr 10 2013
%F A000567 a(6*a(n) + 16*n + 1) = a(6*a(n) + 16*n) + a(6*n + 1). - _Vladimir Shevelev_, Jan 24 2014
%F A000567 a(0) = 0, a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n-1} A005408(A051162(n-1,k)), n >= 1. - _L. Edson Jeffery_, Jul 28 2014
%F A000567 Sum_{n>=1} 1/a(n) = (sqrt(3)*Pi + 9*log(3))/12 = 1.2774090575596367311949534921... . - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Apr 27 2016
%F A000567 From _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Jul 29 2016: (Start)
%F A000567 Inverse binomial transform of A084857.
%F A000567 Sum_{n>=1} (-1)^(n+1)/a(n) = Pi/(2*sqrt(3)) = A093766. (End)
%F A000567 a(n) = n * A016777(n-1) = A053755(n) - A000290(n+1). - _Bruce J. Nicholson_, Aug 10 2017
%F A000567 Product_{n>=2} (1 - 1/a(n)) = 3/4. - _Amiram Eldar_, Jan 21 2021
%F A000567 P(4k+4,n) = ((k+1)*n - k)^2 - (k*n - k)^2 where P(m,n) is the n-th m-gonal number (a generalization of the Apr 10 2013 formula, a(n) = (2*n-1)^2 - (n-1)^2). - _Charlie Marion_, Oct 07 2021
